is there anything i can do to help my dog overcome his fears i recently acquired a male akita that is exremely skittish and pees anytime i take him anywhere what can i do to correct this behavior he is afraid of new people and bolts out of the room anytime he hears a strange noise or someone comes over i think he may have been abused in the past this is what you should do dogs can never learn if they don't try and when they try it once they will know what to do and do the same over you should help him conquer his own fears by take him for walks everyday let him near new people that you know and let them say hi and pet him find a friend that has a dog and let the two play together if there are some weird noises and he gets scared and runs away and you know what the noise is take him to the noise and show him what it is my dog used to be scared of the noise of toilet flushing i took her to the restroom and flushed the toilet in front of her and she's not scared anymore if you want more informations you can contact a vet and i can help you with some questions there are other ways to do all these things but i hope mine helps good luck kevin Toilet Shaggy dog story Kim Possible Washroom Hearing impairment Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Toilet humour Sin City Dog training Xiaolin Showdown Traumatic incident reduction Milton H. Erickson Dead Like Me Dog Cat RuneScape quests The Fairly OddParents The Death Gate Cycle Garfield The Time Machine Urinal Salad Fingers Socialization Bart chalkboard gags Schutzhund Obedience training Euphemism Main characters of Fullmetal Alchemist Coming of Age (TNG episode) Hide and Seek (Stargate Atlantis) Brown Bear Honey and Clover Fecal incontinence English grammar Journey (band) Feral child Aqua Teen Hunger Force Ron and Fez Randomness Pok__mon Live! USS Sea Dog (SS-401) Glen Jacobs Alfred Korzybski Stuttering Characters in the Smurfs Dog agility Ed, Edd n Eddy Azumanga Daioh The Care Bears Adventure in Wonderland Scream (film) Harry Potter an